# 8. この良き日に

Ichika: The picnic blankets are all laid out, Kanade.
Kanade: Thank you, Hoshino. I'm also just about finished getting the tea leaves ready.
Minori: Alright, we've got plenty of hot water, tea leaves, snacks and a great spot! All that's left is to wait for everyone else to arrive!
Kanade: *Nod* Thank you both for helping us with this, Hanasato, Momoi. We really appreciate it.
Airi: You don't need to thank us. All we really did was carry some stuff and put up a few decorations.
Minori: Plus...the real fun hasn't started yet!
Kanade: R-Right... I hope we can be good hosts...
Ichika: I'm starting to get a little nervous...
Ichika: Oh...
Honami: Ichika! Ms. Yoisaki!
Ichika: Hi, Honami...!
Honami: Thank you both for inviting me to this.
Kanade: Thank you for coming.
Ichika: So, um... Please make yourself at home. Do you know where Saki and the others are?
Honami: Oh, they should be here soon.
Saki's Voice: Hi, Ichi! Hi, Hona!
Ichika: Oh, right on cue.
Saki: Thank you very much for inviting me to this♪
Ichika: Welcome, everyone. Hi, Kusanagi!
Nene: H-Hi. I tagged along with the others after bumping into them along the way.
Haruka: It's been a while, Yoisaki. It's me, Kiritani. Ichika invited me.
Haruka: I'm very much looking forward to today's tea party.
Kanade: Yes, please make yourself at home.
Shiho: Oh... You're Yoisaki?
Saki: Cool! I've been wanting to meet you for like ever! This is great! I'm super duper happy!
Kanade: Oh, um... Th-Thank you. It's nice to meet you as well.
Mizuki: Hey, we're here♪
Kanade: Oh, Ena, Mizuki... Welcome.
Ena: Thanks for inviting us, Kanade!
Kanade: Of course. Anyway, please sit. I'll bring you some tea right away.
Mizuki: Okay. Oh, this picnic blanket's super cute! I'm gonna sit here♪
Airi: Alright, is that everyone?
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (I guess Mafuyu couldn't make it...)
Airi: Oh! Hi, Asahina!
Kanade: Huh...?
Kanade: Mafuyu...
Mafuyu: Thank you for inviting me, Kanade.
Mafuyu: I'm looking forward to your tea party.
Kanade: Th-Thank you for coming...
Ichika: Okay, have we all had a chance to grab some snacks...?
Mizuki: Yup! We're all set!
Ichika: Okay, good. That just leaves the tea... How are things going, Kanade?
Kanade: F-Fine, I think... I practiced quite a bit for this...
Kanade: (Okay, I'll start with Ms. Mochizuki's cup...)
Kanade: (First, warm the teapot...and put in two spoonfuls of leaves.)
Kanade: (Pour in some hot water...and let it steep.)
Kanade: (Okay, it should be ready...)
Kanade: Ow...!
Honami: Ms. Yoisaki?! A-Are you okay?
Kanade: I-I'm okay. A drop of hot water landed on me is all.
Honami: O-Okay... Still, would you like me to help with anything?
Kanade: N-No, please let me do this. I invited you here as a guest, so you and the others should be having a nice, relaxing time.
Honami: O-Okay, I understand...
Kanade: Well, here I go...
Mizuki: You can do it, Kanade...!
Kanade: (Hand on the lid to keep it from spilling...)
Kanade: (And pour into the cup... Carefully...)
Kanade: There.
Ena: Th-Thank goodness...!
Mizuki: Geez, Ena, don't be so overprotective. But also, that smells amazing!
Saki: This is so cool! We're outside, but we're still getting the full treatment!
Honami: It smells delicious.
Kanade: Thank you all very much...
Kanade: Anyway, Ms. Mochizuki, here's your cup. While it's still warm...
Honami: Thank you very much. I'll try it now.
Kanade: Your cups will be ready soon, everyone.
Ichika: Oh, Saki, just give me one second. I'll start pouring for you and the others.
Saki: Okay! I can't wait.
Honami: This smells wonderful... Lemon and ginger? Is that right?
Kanade: Yes, it's ginger tea. You said your shoulders were sore, and I was told about how this can help improve blood flow.
Honami: Thank you very much, Ms. Yoisaki. That's so thoughtful of you...
Minori: Oh, what's this one called? It smells so sweet and gentle!
Kanade: It's this shop's own original blend that includes...um, chamomile and lavender... It's supposed to be very soothing.
Ichika: I know you're very busy as idols, so I tried finding something that could help you relax and recover.
Airi: This smells really nice, and it has such a soothing flavor... Thank you both for going through all this trouble!
Ena: Hm? This tea... It tastes like... Peppermint? It's got that refreshing feel to it...
Kanade: Oh, Ena, yours is... Spearmint tea... It's supposed to be refreshing like you said, so it should help you study and sleep better.
Mizuki: Hang on. Did you two get different types of tea for everybody here?
Kanade: Yes, we made our choices based on things you told us.
Ena: Wait, you put that much thought into this...?
Ena: So, you got this just for me...? I don't know what to say!
Ena: I'm going to savor every drop!
Kanade: O-Okay, but I can always pour you some more...
Kanade: Phew... That's everyone for now.
Kanade: (They all seem to be having a nice, relaxing time.)
Saki: Wait, whoa...! You're the “Ena” I've heard so much about, Shinonome?! The one who's in the same group as Asahina?!
Saki: I've seen your videos! I love them so much!!
Honami: Hehe. Ena's really an incredible artist. You should see some of her drawings and paintings.
Shiho: I've seen her art too, and I remember being blown away by it.
Ena: Th-They're really not that great. Yes, I can draw, but only because I attend an art class.
Mizuki: You say that, but you sure sound pretty happy.
Nene: It's a tea party, so... I should try to talk to some people.
Nene: B-But, who...?
Minori: Nene!
Nene: Huh? Hanasato and Momoi...?
Minori: Ichika invited you, right? Welcome!
Airi: Sorry for not coming to talk to you sooner. Here, let's have some of these snacks together!
Nene: O-Oh, okay...
Mizuki: Hey, everyone! Let's all talk over here!
Airi: Oh, okay! Let's go, you two!
Nene: Huh? M-Me too...? Are you sure?
Minori: Of course! Come on! Let's go!
Nene: O-Okay...
Kanade: (Thank goodness. They all seem to be enjoying themselves. But...)
Mafuyu: Kanade.
Kanade: Mafuyu...
Kanade: Thank you again for coming. So, how's the tea...?
Mafuyu: I feel a bit relaxed.
Kanade: I'm glad to hear it...
Kanade: Yours is linden tea, Mafuyu. It's supposed to have a very soothing floral flavor.
Kanade: I'm not sure if I steeped it properly, but I hope it helped a little.
Mafuyu: You really got a particular kind of tea just for me?
Kanade: Huh? Oh, yes. Let me know if you'd like some more.
Mafuyu: Okay...
Kanade: I'm sorry if I caused you any trouble, Mafuyu.
Kanade: But I'm really glad that you decided to join us for this tea party...
Mafuyu: You didn't cause me any trouble.
Mafuyu: I can't say whether or not it's this tea, but... I don't feel all that bothered.
Mafuyu: Also...
Kanade: Huh...?
Mafuyu: I wouldn't mind doing something like this again.
Kanade: Oh...
Kanade: (At first, I had so much trouble figuring out what to get everyone...)
Kanade: (But I'm glad we gave it so much thought and decided to hold this tea party.)
Kanade: (And I'm incredibly glad that everyone's getting this chance to take a break from their busy schedules to have a nice, relaxing time.)
